24/12/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Police in Tirana arrested a citizen Wednesday (December 23rd) wanted by US authorities for stealing and selling luxury vehicles in the United States. Francesk Pashko Pashku of Shkodra is wanted for a series of crimes committed in 1997 and 1998 and was hiding in Albania before Interpol located him, police said. He allegedly stole cars in New York and sold them in Florida. (Lajmifundit, Top Channel, Balkan Web - 23/12/09)
